"Coldea G., Stoica I.-A., Puşcaş M., Ursu T., Oprea A.","Alpine-subalpine species richness of the Romanian Carpathians and the current conservation status of rare species",2009,"Biodiversity and Conservation","18","6",,"1441","1458",,,10.1007/s10531-008-9488-z,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-65649153019&partnerID=40&md5=b9b485147e6d47e8f4970bb676f6fb4c","Department of Plant Ecology, Institute of Biological Research, Republicii Street, No. 48, 4000015 Cluj-Napoca, Romania; Botanical Garden, Babes-Bolyai University, Cluj-Napoca, Romania; Botanical Garden, Al. I. Cuza University, Iasi, Romania","Coldea, G., Department of Plant Ecology, Institute of Biological Research, Republicii Street, No. 48, 4000015 Cluj-Napoca, Romania; Stoica, I.-A., Department of Plant Ecology, Institute of Biological Research, Republicii Street, No. 48, 4000015 Cluj-Napoca, Romania; Puşcaş, M., Botanical Garden, Babes-Bolyai University, Cluj-Napoca, Romania; Ursu, T., Department of Plant Ecology, Institute of Biological Research, Republicii Street, No. 48, 4000015 Cluj-Napoca, Romania; Oprea, A., Botanical Garden, Al. I. Cuza University, Iasi, Romania","In the context of global warming, alpine-subalpine plant species are some of the most threatened. The distribution of these species in the Romanian Carpathians is centralized and analyzed for the first time. A network with 472 grid cells of 12.5 × 11.5 km (6? latitude × 10? longitude) has been used to register the distribution of 550 selected high mountain taxa. The analysis starts with a brief description of the most important determinants of alpine-subalpine species richness, continues with a comparison between the different sub groups of the Romanian Carpathians and a discussion of their particularities. The purpose of the paper is to identify areas in need of protection as well as rare and vulnerable species outside the network of protected areas. A description of the current network of protected areas from the Romanian Carpathians is provided, with ideas for improvement. © 2008 Springer Science+Business Media B.V.","Endemic species; Floristic diversity; Rare species; Romanian Carpathians; Subalpine-alpine taxa; Vulnerable taxa","endangered species; endemic species; protected area; rare species; species diversity; species richness; Carpathians; Eurasia; Europe; Italy; Lazio; Roma [Lazio]; Rome; Southern Europe",,,,,,"Al, B., (1967) Flora Şi Vegetaţia Munţilor Bucegi, , Bucureşti; Birks, H.J.B., Statistical approaches to interpreting diversity patterns in the Norwegian mountain flora (1996) Ecography, 19 (3), pp. 332-340; Al, B., (1959) Flora Şi Vegetaţia Vǎii Sebeşului, , Bucureşti; Boşcaiu, N., (1971) Flora Şi Vegetaţia Munţilor Ţarcu, , Godeanu şi Cernei Bucureşti; Bruun, H.H., Moen, J., Angerbjorn, A., Environmental correlates of meso-scale plant species richness in the province of Härjedalen, Sweden (2003) Biodiversity and Conservation, 12 (10), pp. 2025-2041. , DOI 10.1023/A:1024159932021; Gh, C., (1990) Munţii Rodnei, , Studiu geobotanic Bucureşti; Gh, C., Prodrome des associations végétales des Carpates du sud-est (Carpates roumanies) (1991) Documents Phytosociologiques N. 5, 13, pp. 317-539; Gh, C., Nagy, L., Grabherr, G., Körner, C., Thompson, D., The Alpine flora and vegetation of the Romanian Carpathians (2003) Alpine Biodiversity in Europe, pp. 65-73. , Springer Berlin; Şt, C., Csürös Kaptalan, M., Resmeriţǎ, I., Die ökologischen kennzahlen: Feuchtigkeit, temperatur, Bodenreaktion und der Futterwert der wichtigsten Arten an den Weiden Transsylvaniens (Rumänien) (1967) Studia Univ. Babeş-bolyai, Ser. Biol. Cluj, i, pp. 21-27. , II: 9 -14; Dihoru, G., Pârvu, C., (1987) Plante Endemice în Flora României, , Bucureşti; Ehrendorfer, F., Harmann, U., Vorschläge zu einer floristischen Kartierung Mitteleuropas (1965) Ber Dtsch Bot Ges, 78, pp. 35-50; Ellenberg, H., Weber, H.E., Düll, R., Wirth, V., Werner, W., Paulissen, D., (1992) Zeigerwerte von Pflanzen in Mitteleuropa, , Verl